title: In photos: The 50th anniversary of the U.S.-backed coup in Chile
description: On Sept. 11, 1973, Chilean Gen. Augusto Pinochet overthrew the elected government of President Salvador Allende and ushered in 17 years of military rule.

title: Anger and despair in quake-ravaged Morocco as communities wait for help
description: Residents were using their bare hands to pull loved ones from the rubble after Friday’s 6.8 quake in Morocco. In most places, there was no sign of rescue teams.

title: Ukraine live briefing: G-20 declaration avoids criticizing Russia; Kyiv and Tokyo discuss security pact
description: The declaration from Group of 20 leaders in New Delhi stopped short of criticizing Russia for the war, but called on members not to forcefully take territory.

title: In time of war, Russia turns up aggression on transgender citizens
description: Putin once couched his opposition to LGBTQ and trans people as a matter of protecting children, now it is a matter of national security.

title: Morocco earthquake live briefing: More than 2,000 dead; king quiet in disaster’s aftermath
description: The 6.8-magnitude earthquake struck about 47 miles southeast of Marrakesh late Friday, crumbling buildings and killing thousands.

title: Hot Dubai stays cool with indoor skiing and snow cinemas
description: From ice baths on the beach to indoor ski camps, and snow movie theaters, here’s how people stay cool in one of the hottest and wealthiest cities.

title: Morocco earthquake survivors saw houses crumble and neighbors fall
description: A tourist and a resident of Marrakesh said they saw bodies, smoke and rubble as they fled to safety from the Morocco earthquake Friday night.
